$$Y^1_1(-\theta,-\phi) = -\sin\theta e^{i\phi}$$
where $\theta$ is the polar angle measured from the $\hat{\mathbf{k}}$ direction and $\phi$ is the azimuthal angle.

The negative sign just indicates that the probability is maximized when the neutron spin is in the southern hemisphere, which makes sense physically.

